{
  "texts": [
    "HSI is a technology that combines both spectroscopic and photography approaches into a single system, allowing it to gather both spectral and spatial information about the studied object.",
    "HSI is a promising technology that enables the rapid and accurate detection of spectral and spatial information.",
    "To derive spectral, textural and morphological information from high-dimensional HSI data, chemometric approaches are necessary (Temiz and Ulas, 2021).",
    "In this regard, the combined use of non-destructive optical imaging and spectroscopic techniques for evaluating food safety and quality analysis is gaining popularity.",
    "Shafiee et al. (2016) investigated the use of HSI system and data mining-based classifiers to detect honey adulteration."
  ]
}